        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:43PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 443 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Lexa, or near St Francis National Park, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena-West Helena, St Francis National Park, Lexa, Lagrange,
Jeffersonville, Raggio, Huma, Haleside, Fox Island, Quarles, Austin,
Wycamp, Latour, Phillips Bayou, Whitehall, Cypress Corner, Tongin,
and Delta Heritage Trails State Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
